Thunderous applause trailed the performance by a Fulani cultural troupe at the Eagle Square, venue of today’s Democracy Day celebration in Abuja. The maiden Democracy Day celebration is being witnessed by President Muhammadu Buhari, world leaders, traditional rulers, Senate President, Ahmad Lawan; Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila, governors and other dignitaries from within and outside the country. For about 15 minutes, the cultural troupe thrilled dignitaries with their brilliant performance, Daily Trust reports. Inside Ogidi’s dazzling cultural festival Gospel Alhaji, Omo Awe, others thrill at sallah Harvest of dance at annual Ogidi Day Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin